  "body": "When using a 'datetime-local' field, setting just the date doesn't register a change of value (so when setting to no value react doesn't know there has been a change).\n\nA fix would be to always set the value of datetime fields even when the virtual dom shows no change - or just to accept it as a limitation.\n\n``` jsx\n// An example\n<input type=\"datetime-local\" value={this.state.date} onChange={(evt) => {\n    this.setState({date: evt.target.value})\n}} />\n```\n\n(Tested on Chrome only (not supported on FF))\n",
